in linux file permision determine who can read , write and execute file and directories
command is chmod -->
chmod --> change permission

1) symbloic notation

who = u(user/owner), g(group), o(others)
operate = +(add), -( remove), = (set)
permission = r(read), w(write), x(execute)

2) octal notation
x->owner/user, y ->group, z->others.
permissions = 4-> read, 2->write, 1->execute



chown --> change ownership or files and directories
example:->
chown user/owner filename/directories
